@Node "Installation" "Mailtext_mcc.guide/Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   What you need to use the Mailtext package:

   * a minimum of Kickstart and Workbench 2.04

   * a minimum of MUI 2.3, although MUI 3.3 or above is recommended for
     the use of the preferences plugin Mailtext.mcp

   * Crawling.mcc by Klaus Melchior for Mailtext.mcp (this is optional,
     Mailtext.mcp will also work without).

   For installation you should use the supplied installer script which
will setup all you need to use the Mailtext package.


@EndNode

@Node "Configuration" "Mailtext_mcc.guide/Configuration"
@Toc "Main"

Configuration
*************

   If you are using MUI 3.3 or above, most features of Mailtext may be
configured to fit your needs using the supplied Mailtext.mcp, a plugin
module for the MUI Preferences system.

   The plugin makes use of MUIs Bubblehelp system, so I will not
explain the features here, just one note:

   An important thing to know when configuring Mailtext are what is
meant with "introducing char" and "terminating char", so please have a
look at the following example (let + be an attributecharacter '*', '/',
'_' or '#'):

        +Text+
        ^    ^
        |    |
        |    +- the terminating char
        |
        +- the introducing char

   With this is mind, it should be pretty easy to configure Mailtext to
your needs.


@EndNode

@Node "Developers" "Mailtext_mcc.guide/Developers"
@Toc "Main"

Developers
**********

   If you consider using Mailtext in one of your own programs, please
have a look at the @{"Copyright" Link "Copyright"} first.

   You are really welcome to use Mailtext in your own projects, but the
needed headerfiles for C, Oberon and Modula-2 are *only* available on
request, as I would like to know which applications are using the class.

   For requesting the developer package, have a look at @{"Author" Link "Author"} to find
out about ways to contact me.


@EndNode

